==1173825== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==1173825== Copyright (C) 2002-2017, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.

/home/ankammer/Cursus42/minishell> cat Makefile
==1173827== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==1173827== Copyright (C) 2002-2017, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.
==1173827== Using Valgrind-3.18.1 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info
==1173827== Command: /usr/bin/cat Makefile
==1173827== 
NAME = minishell

OBJ_DIR = obj
SRC_DIR = srcs
BUILTIN_DIR = $(SRC_DIR)/builtin
EXEC_DIR = $(SRC_DIR)/exec


# Définition des sources
SRC = $(SRC_DIR)/fonction.c $(SRC_DIR)/main.c $(SRC_DIR)/init_node.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/tokenisation.c $(SRC_DIR)/verif_line.c $(SRC_DIR)/automate.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/here_doc.c $(SRC_DIR)/find_var.c $(SRC_DIR)/sort_cmds.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/init_tcmds.c $(SRC_DIR)/sort_cmds_utils.c $(SRC_DIR)/free.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/init_t_redir.c $(SRC_DIR)/expandornot.c $(SRC_DIR)/init_expand.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/get_env.c $(SRC_DIR)/get_final_line.c $(SRC_DIR)/mallocs.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/init.c $(SRC_DIR)/ft_error.c $(SRC_DIR)/token_utils.c \
      $(SRC_DIR)/token_utils2.c $(SRC_DIR)/utils.c $(SRC_DIR)/init_env.c \
      $(BUILTIN_DIR)/cd.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/echo.c  $(SRC_DIR)/builtins_or_not.c \
	  $(BUILTIN_DIR)/export.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/unset.c $(SRC_DIR)/modif_env.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/env.c \
	  $(BUILTIN_DIR)/exit.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/pwd.c $(EXEC_DIR)/open_and_close.c \
	  $(EXEC_DIR)/pipex_process.c $(EXEC_DIR)/pipex.c $(EXEC_DIR)/utils.c $(EXEC_DIR)/utils2.c $(SRC_DIR)/signal.c 

# Génération des objets en fonction des sources (respecte les sous-dossiers)
OBJ = $(SRC:$(SRC_DIR)/%.c=$(OBJ_DIR)/%.o)
DEPS = $(OBJ:.o=.d)

LIBFT = ./libft/libft.a

CC = cc
CFLAGS = -Wall -Werror -Wextra -g3
LD_FLAGS = -lreadline -lncurses -lcurses

LIB_SHELL = minishell.a

all: $(NAME)

$(NAME): $(OBJ) $(LIBFT) $(LIB_SHELL)
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) $(OBJ) $(LIBFT) $(LD_FLAGS) -o $(NAME)

$(LIB_SHELL): $(OBJ)
	ar rcs $(LIB_SHELL) $(OBJ)

-include $(DEPS)

# Règle de compilation pour les objets, avec création de dossiers si nécessaire
$(OBJ_DIR)/%.o: $(SRC_DIR)/%.c | $(OBJ_DIR) $(OBJ_DIR)/builtin $(OBJ_DIR)/exec
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -MMD -MP -c $< -o $@

# Création des dossiers d'objets pour chaque sous-dossier
$(OBJ_DIR):
	mkdir -p $(OBJ_DIR)

$(OBJ_DIR)/builtin:
	mkdir -p $(OBJ_DIR)/builtin 
$(OBJ_DIR)/exec:	
	mkdir -p $(OBJ_DIR)/exec

# Compilation de la libft
$(LIBFT):
	make -C ./libft

clean:
	rm -rf $(OBJ_DIR)
	make -C ./libft clean
    
fclean: clean
	rm -f $(NAME)
	rm -f $(LIB_SHELL)
	make -C ./libft fclean

re: fclean all==1173827==

==1175302== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==1175302== Copyright (C) 2002-2017, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.
==1175302== Using Valgrind-3.18.1 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info
==1175302== Command: ./minishell
==1175302== 
/home/ankammer/Cursus42/minishell> cat Makefile | cat -e | cat -e
==1175303== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==1175303== Copyright (C) 2002-2017, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.
==1175303== Using Valgrind-3.18.1 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info
==1175303== Command: /usr/bin/cat Makefile
==1175303== 
==1175305== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==1175305== Copyright (C) 2002-2017, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.
==1175304== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==1175304== Copyright (C) 2002-2017, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.
==1175304== Using Valgrind-3.18.1 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info
==1175304== Command: /usr/bin/cat -e
==1175304== 
==1175305== Using Valgrind-3.18.1 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info
==1175305== Command: /usr/bin/cat -e
==1175305== 
NAME = minishell$$
$$
OBJ_DIR = obj$$
SRC_DIR = srcs$$
BUILTIN_DIR = $(SRC_DIR)/builtin$$
EXEC_DIR = $(SRC_DIR)/exec$$
$$
$$
# DM-CM-)finition des sources$$
SRC = $(SRC_DIR)/fonction.c $(SRC_DIR)/main.c $(SRC_DIR)/init_node.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/tokenisation.c $(SRC_DIR)/verif_line.c $(SRC_DIR)/automate.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/here_doc.c $(SRC_DIR)/find_var.c $(SRC_DIR)/sort_cmds.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/init_tcmds.c $(SRC_DIR)/sort_cmds_utils.c $(SRC_DIR)/free.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/init_t_redir.c $(SRC_DIR)/expandornot.c $(SRC_DIR)/init_expand.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/get_env.c $(SRC_DIR)/get_final_line.c $(SRC_DIR)/mallocs.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/init.c $(SRC_DIR)/ft_error.c $(SRC_DIR)/token_utils.c \$$
      $(SRC_DIR)/token_utils2.c $(SRC_DIR)/utils.c $(SRC_DIR)/init_env.c \$$
      $(BUILTIN_DIR)/cd.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/echo.c  $(SRC_DIR)/builtins_or_not.c \$$
	  $(BUILTIN_DIR)/export.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/unset.c $(SRC_DIR)/modif_env.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/env.c \$$
	  $(BUILTIN_DIR)/exit.c $(BUILTIN_DIR)/pwd.c $(EXEC_DIR)/open_and_close.c \$$
	  $(EXEC_DIR)/pipex_process.c $(EXEC_DIR)/pipex.c $(EXEC_DIR)/utils.c $(EXEC_DIR)/utils2.c $(SRC_DIR)/signal.c $$
$$
# GM-CM-)nM-CM-)ration des objets en fonction des sources (respecte les sous-dossiers)$$
OBJ = $(SRC:$(SRC_DIR)/%.c=$(OBJ_DIR)/%.o)$$
DEPS = $(OBJ:.o=.d)$$
$$
LIBFT = ./libft/libft.a$$
$$
CC = cc$$
CFLAGS = -Wall -Werror -Wextra -g3$$
LD_FLAGS = -lreadline -lncurses -lcurses$$
$$
LIB_SHELL = minishell.a$$
$$
all: $(NAME)$$
$$
$(NAME): $(OBJ) $(LIBFT) $(LIB_SHELL)$$
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) $(OBJ) $(LIBFT) $(LD_FLAGS) -o $(NAME)$$
$$
$(LIB_SHELL): $(OBJ)$$
	ar rcs $(LIB_SHELL) $(OBJ)$$
$$
-include $(DEPS)$$
$$
# RM-CM-(gle de compilation pour les objets, avec crM-CM-)ation de dossiers si nM-CM-)cessaire$$
$(OBJ_DIR)/%.o: $(SRC_DIR)/%.c | $(OBJ_DIR) $(OBJ_DIR)/builtin $(OBJ_DIR)/exec$$
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -MMD -MP -c $< -o $@$$
$$
# CrM-CM-)ation des dossiers d'objets pour chaque sous-dossier$$
$(OBJ_DIR):$$
	mkdir -p $(OBJ_DIR)$$
$$
$(OBJ_DIR)/builtin:$$
	mkdir -p $(OBJ_DIR)/builtin $$
$(OBJ_DIR)/exec:	$$
	mkdir -p $(OBJ_DIR)/exec$$
$$
# Compilation de la libft$$
$(LIBFT):$$
	make -C ./libft$$
$$
clean:$$
	rm -rf $(OBJ_DIR)$$
	make -C ./libft clean$$
    $$
fclean: clean$$
	rm -f $(NAME)$$
	rm -f $(LIB_SHELL)$$
	make -C ./libft fclean$$
$$
re: fclean all==1175303==
